#part a
library(dplyr)
#to increase accuracy we filter movies that were voted less than 
# half of total number of votes average
rating %>% group_by(MovieID) %>% 
  summarise(mean_rate=mean(Rating,na.rm=TRUE),count=n()) %>% 
  filter(count > 0.5*mean(count,na.rm=TRUE)) %>% 
  mutate(rank=as.integer(rank(-mean_rate)))->q1

#first we choose movies with highest rating average 
popular_movie=q1$MovieID[which(q1$rank==1)]
print("most popular movie")
## [1] "most popular movie"
movie$Title[which(movie$MovieId==popular_movie)]
## [1] "Shawshank Redemption, The (1994)"
#partb

library(RColorBrewer)
names=movie %>% select(Title)
words=str_sub(names$Title, 1,-7)

final = words %>% 
  str_replace_all("\"","") %>% 
  str_replace_all("[[:punct:]]","") %>% 
  str_split(pattern = "\\s") %>% 
  unlist() %>% 
  str_to_lower() %>% 
  removeWords(., stopwords('en')) %>% 
  str_trim() %>% 
  table() %>% 
  as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors = F)

colnames(final) = c("word","count")

final = final %>% arrange(desc(count)) %>% 
  filter(nchar(word)>3)

wordcloud(final$word,final$count, random.order = FALSE, colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))
